headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 35 points and Chris Paul added 16 in the Phoenix Suns’ 101-97 overtime victory against the Charlotte Hornets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker's 35 points leads Suns past Hornets 101-97 in OT

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored seven of his 23 points in the final two minutes and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Toronto Raptors 122-117 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum, Lillard lead Blazers past Raptors 122-117

headlines.description: — Aaron Gordon scored 13 points in his debut with Denver, and the Nuggets beat the Atlanta Hawks 126-102 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gordon scores 13 in Denver debut, a 126-102 win over Hawks

events.name: Orlando Magic at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Dennis Schröder scored 24 points, Kyle Kuzma added 21 and the Los Angeles Lakers rallied in the fourth quarter to defeat the Orlando Magic 96-93 Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers hold off Magic 96-93, win again without LeBron, Davis
